FBIS3-29727 "dreas035_c_94005" FBIS-EAS-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 North Korea South's Opposition Urges Cancellation of Patriots SK2002082994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0819 GMT 20 Feb 94 SK2002082994 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Pyongyang, February 20 (KCNA) -- The opposition Democratic Party of South Korea in a statement released by its spokesman Saturday urged the U.S. Government to drop the projected deployment of Patriot missiles in South Korea, which might provoke the North, a radio report from Seoul said. The statement also demanded that the South Korean authorities pursue a self-determined diplomacy for the relaxation of the tensions on the Korean peninsula, said the radio.
